modified:
(b) Quarterly payments of $312,500 each will be made, commencing on September 15, 1999, and continuing on each December 15, March 15, June 15, and September 15 thereafter during the Term. However, if any of the following conditions arise, the obligation to make these payments may cease:

   (i) If the Agreement is terminated in accordance with Section 6 of the Agreement prior to a due date, no subsequent quarterly payments will be required after the effective date of such termination.

   (ii) If the Minimum Revenue Target for the first year of the Term is not achieved by the first anniversary of the Effective Date, no quarterly payments will be payable until such time as the Minimum Revenue Target for the first year of the Term is achieved. Once this target is reached, future quarterly payments will resume on the schedule and in the amount set forth above for the duration of the Term.

   (iii) If the aggregate Minimum Revenue Targets for both the first and second years of the Term are not achieved by the second anniversary of the Effective Date, no quarterly payments will be made during the second year of the Term until the aggregate Minimum Revenue Target is achieved. After this target is reached, future quarterly payments will resume on the schedule and in the amount set forth above for the duration of the Term.

   In the event that the Minimum Revenue Target for the first year of the Agreement is not achieved within the first year, the parties will engage in good faith negotiations to adjust downwards the quarterly payments.

                                    RESPONSIBILITIES REGARDING FUNDS:

This agreement outlines the responsibilities of both parties in relation to funding for our joint marketing programs. Instead of us committing to providing a specific amount or percentage of funds, we propose that each party contributes according to their own discretion and available resources at any given time. While we encourage active participation from both parties, we recognize that the ultimate responsibility for funding may occasionally need to be shouldered individually based on the financial capabilities of each party at a particular moment. We believe this approach fosters a more collaborative and responsive partnership, ensuring our joint marketing efforts remain effective and sustainable over time.
